name: Martina Seidl
content: Martina Seidl TNF / INF FMV team contact software publications teaching jobs Univ.Prof. Dr. Martina Seidl phone: +43 732 2468 5750 mail: Martina.Seidl@jku.at office hours: by appointment address: Institute for Symbolic Artificial Intelligence Johannes Kepler University Altenbergerstr. 69 4040 Linz, Austria I am professor of the Institut für Symbolic Artificial Intelligence and associated to the Institute for Formal Models and Verification as interim head, both at the Johannes Kepler Universität Linz. Before I came to Linz in 2010, I worked at the Business Informatics Group of the Vienna University of Technology. Research Interests Quantified Boolean Formulas Automated Reasoning Model Evolution Model Engineering Formal Verification of Software Models Ongoing Projects Doctoral College in LogicCS (associated faculty member) National Research Network RiSE (SHiNE, 2nd phase, co-PI) Finished Projects FAME (principal investigator) AMOR - Adaptable Model Versioning (technical head) ModelCVS (researcher) Publications List of publications at DBLP List of selected publications
